column2: Very hot- 90+ F- baby ducks getting big- had rain 07/23- light winds 5 mph- lots of people on the lake.
Cool but sunny + beautiful. 65 F. windy (35 mph).  About 60 geese lifted off lake for points south.
Temp 75 degrees- clear- very dry- trying to cloud up but no rain.  Sea gulls very busy.  Loons nesting so. bay.

We need a loon nesting sign on our little island.  Loon off nest.  People were walking around nest so no baby loons this year.  Too bad!  rain for 2 days so water May improve.  Temp 80 degrees- partly cloudy- but very nice.
Mostly sunny- 80 degrees- slight breeze- lots of lake traffic.  No geese on lake.  Water looks good but smells fishy.
85 degrees- sunny. high traffic. dry but did have some rain during the week.  Lots of geese on lake.
Sunny- 4 boats on lake. water warm. gulls floating on lake- loons on lake- 20 geese on my lot feeding on clover. lots of turtles sitting on lily pads in south bay.
Sunny- no traffic on lake.  Geese and ducks gone. cold- 40 degrees F.- white caps on lake. some gulls left. most people have removed docks.
Beautiful day.  Sunny but clouds rolling in - will rain soon.  Some breeze.  Geese on lake.  Have not seen loons yet.  No one else on lake.  Lots of gulls.
Bright sunny day.  No clouds in sight.  Seen some seagulls- loons- bald eagle.  At depth of 21.2 feet.
85 F.  Beautiful day- clear.  1 boat- 2 pontoons- geese on lawn this morning.  Some swimmers.  Windy on lake- but no white caps.
